Having sex is great and all but it’s not something that should be taken lightly, unless a woman was raped or something to that extreme then ofc it’s a different scenario but for the most part, take responsibility for your actions. It’s not fair to terminate the future of a future child (wether their a fetus or not because I know that’s a huge argument the way I see it is it’s still a fetus with a potential to do great things and live a life of their own) because of someone’s negligence but that being said I know I can never 100% understand unless it happens to me but that’s just how I feel

snippet.textDisplay:
I think this episode is a bit skewed towards the teen dads that actually were there for their baby, so that the episode makers could get in contact with them as a 'teen dad' rather than having to ask the girl who the father was and contact them that way.
If the episode were about teen mothers, it would be different, since teen mothers have to do something about a pregnancy and, if they keep the baby, are forced into being there for the child (whatever they might feel about doing so), but teen fathers have the ability to walk away.
I think if it were possible to have gotten in contact with a wider selection of teen dads, some of whom weren't active in accepting their role and responsibilities, this episode would have been very different.
